# Build Configuration & Development Workflow

## Vite Configuration
- Uses [@crxjs/vite-plugin](mdc:vite.config.ts) for Chrome extension building
- Configured with path aliases: `@/*` â†’ `src/*`
- Includes static copy plugin for locale files
- ZIP packaging for release builds

## TypeScript Configuration
- Root config in [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) with project references
- App-specific config in [tsconfig.app.json](mdc:tsconfig.app.json)
- Node-specific config in [tsconfig.node.json](mdc:tsconfig.node.json)
- Path mapping configured for `@/*` alias

## Development Scripts
- `pnpm dev:extension` - Development mode with hot reload
- `pnpm build:extension` - Production build
- `pnpm test` - Run Vitest tests
- `pnpm preview` - Preview production build

## Dependencies
- **Core**: Vue 3, TypeScript, Vite
- **Chrome Extension**: @crxjs/vite-plugin, @types/chrome
- **QR Code**: @zxing/browser
- **State**: Pinia
- **UI**: toastify-js for notifications
- **Testing**: Vitest with happy-dom

## Build Output
- Extension files in `dist/` directory
- Release ZIP in `release/release.zip`
- Locale files copied to build output
- Service worker and content scripts properly bundled
